21 and over
$13 in advance / $15 at the door

THARUN SANKAR
Tharun Sankar is a producer, songwriter, and jazz trumpet player on a mission to make his mark on San Francisco's independent music scene. In this show, he debuts his third EP, Foliage, a deeply moving, personal, and original work which at the same time manages to be his most universal and resonant writing yet. He aims to capture the harmonic sophistication of modern jazz and temper it with a strong sense of simplicity, minimalism, and emotional honesty drawn from pop and EDM. Hear it for the first time live at this album release show, backed by the up-and-coming jazz-funk band Mint Glaze.

View this event on Partiful at https://partiful.com/e/NpmreLAnL3ipIktT0xpo

On February 5th, Bluesky opened up to everyone. Since then, 1.6M users have joined, bringing the network up to nearly 5M. Log off for a moment and join some of the team in SF to celebrate this occasion!

Drinks and refreshments will be provided.

Join Bluesky (no invite code required): bsky.app

If you‚Äôre a dev, we are cohosting a hackathon Sunday, Feb 25 with skygaze.io and you should come:  https://partiful.com/e/AiscT5PsNTIrxNq58M5q
 
 ---- 

Bluesky is building an open social internet. On the surface, it's an app that works a lot like Twitter, but it's not controlled by a single company. On centralized social apps, you have a single black-box algorithm, designed to keep you scrolling. On Bluesky, we've built the foundation for anyone to build a feed, moderation service, or a host of other services. Our communication systems are a reflection of our democracy, and we think social should be made by the people for the people.

View this event on Partiful at https://partiful.com/e/TPHbpcKn3RyzQ0s3RxRY

Pull up to Demo Day if you want to share a passion project with fellow creators at Berkeley!

You'll get 1-2 minutes to present something, and there'll be a fair after the presentations to hang out with other people. :)

üö® Demo recordings are due by Sunday at 4 PM. Submit at berkeleydemo.day/submit. üö®

Who:

Anyone who has something to share! You're welcome even if you don't consider yourself a ‚Äúcreator,‚Äù are awkward (we are too!), or aren't certain of what you'll be demoing yet.

What:

Your passion project can be anything‚Äîsomething you knit, coded, designed, or built with your own two hands. Just make sure it's something you're genuinely passionate about outside of school, campus clubs, and work. (No startups or businesses, please!)

Why:

- The vibes are sure to be immaculate, so hopefully you'll make friends with other fun and interesting people
- It's something to work towards if you've been procrastinating over your passion project
- It's a great way to beat the dead week blues


A few ground rules:

1. ‚ÄãAct like a host, include people in conversations, talk to people even if they're strangers, offer to help out and clean up, and most importantly, don't come to network! If you're here to network we will be very sad. :(

2. Don't ask people about their major, their classes, their year, or what school they go to‚Äîtalk about your interests outside of academics!

Berkeley Demo Day is heavily inspired by a similar event hosted by Socratica (https://socrati.ca) at UWaterloo: https://twitter.com/jonxuxu/status/1644149531661983747. Huge thanks to Aadil Ali and Jonathan Xu for helping us organize this!

2024-09-12.description:
View this event on Partiful at https://partiful.com/e/pYFQpYTrotMrwvkZLLNq

We believe in the magic of bringing our community together around unique, shared experiences. This "Weird Wednesday" experience is one of our experiments: a pop-up sci-fi "drive-in" theater in San Francisco. We will bring together our friends and founders of Long Journey for crave-able movie snacks and mind-bending inspiration.

Don't worry, you don't need a car just to come for this pop-up ‚Äî we wanted to evoke the feeling of a "drive-in theater" as we believe there is magic to sharing the experience with someone sitting in the front seat with you, your BYO candy, and the debrief/discussion after the movie.

We will be taking over the timeless Roxie Theater and also the Little Roxie for "Weird Wednesday." We hope you can attend and invite you to bring a +1 to bring into our community!

Our Journey:
- 6:00 PM - Theater Doors (and Snack Concession Stand) Open + Check-in
- 6:30 PM - Bubbe Ritual + Sci-Fi Screening Begins
- 7:00 PM - Theater Doors Close 
- 9:15 PM - Nerd Sessions (Discussions on the Movie)
- 9:30 PM - Sci Fi Theater Ends with Open Mingling
